This paper deals with distributed medium access control in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses optimization problems and iterative methods, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for time-synchronous multichannel TDMA coordination, which could fall under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper uses simulations and experiments to evaluate the proposed scheme, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves empirical evaluation of a proposed algorithm.
